cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel end-to-end model for aspect-based rating prediction using natural language processing techniques. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper deals with analyzing user reviews to predict ratings and discover coherent aspects of reviews. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses max-margin losses for joint item and user embedding learning and a dual-headed architecture. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a model that can be used in a recommender system. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the least likely category as the paper does not deal with security or cryptography.
